 Educational Background



 


Louisiana State University - Graduate School of Banking






 


Coastal Carolina University

                  The Community and Business Engagement (CoBE) Institute is a chance to connect the subject matter expertise of our faculty.                





 Career History



Secretary & Executive Vice President

                                    2010 - Current                


Carolina Financial Corp.


                  Carolina Financial Corp. operates as a holding company. It provides commercial banking services to individuals and small-to medium-sized businesses. The company operates through the following segments: Community Banking, Wholesale Mortgage Banking, and Other. The Community Banking segment provides traditional banking services offered through CresCom Bank. The Mortgage Banking segment provides mortgage loan origination and servicing offered through Crescent Mortgage. The Other segment provides managerial and operational support to the other business segments through Carolina Services and Carolina Financial. It offers various deposit products including checking accounts, savings accounts, money market accounts, time deposits, certificates of deposit and commercial lending. The company was founded by John D. Russ in February 1997 and is headquartered in Wilmington, DE.                




Secretary & Executive Vice President

                                    1997 - Current                


CresCom Bank


                  CresCom Bank’s origins were derived from the consolidation of Crescent Bank and Community FirstBank. The firm's roots run deep along the South Carolina coast.Both Community FirstBank (Charleston) and Crescent Bank (Myrtle Beach) were founded by local business leaders committed to building successful banks in both cities under the umbrella of parent holding company Carolina Financial Corporation. The reason for both banks forming was the same: as a response to several large bank mergers that left few community banking choices for area residents and businesses.Carolina Financial Corporation was founded in 1997 in Charleston and quickly introduced Community FirstBank. Expanding over the course of 15 years, the bank grew to six locations throughout the area, providing banking products and exceptional service to the Greater Charleston market.In order to bring the community banking atmosphere back to Myrtle Beach, Carolina Financial Corporation partnered with business leaders in the Myrtle Beach area to form another community bank – Crescent Bank. Through the years, Crescent Bank grew to four full-service locations to meet the banking needs of Grand Strand residents and businesses. After 11 years of operating the banks as two independent banks, the Board of Directors and management recognized consolidating the two banks into one would create more opportunities and better service to their customers.As a result, on March 26, 2012, the firm's sister banks consolidated to become one bank – CresCom Bank. The name and the logo pay tribute to its former brands by using elements from both Crescent and Community FirstBank, along with the Crescent Moon, which is such an iconic brand element of the state.Consolidated, now CresCom Bank has 14 locations along the coast of South Carolina. Offering a strong core of banking products and services and a committed group of community leaders, management and personnel, CresCom Bank remains committed to warm, exceptional service and a strong knowledge of local businesses and economic trends.It’s this dedication that makes \"\"Have a nice bank.\"\" more than just a slogan, but a commitment to service. This, combined with the years of experience and unique understanding of financial opportunities along coastal South Carolina, makes CresCom Bank the perfect fit for customers' personal or business financial needs.The company believes that community involvement is a vital key to understanding the needs of both the Grand Strand and the Charleston markets. They strive to know customers by customers' name and not just a number. And, as always, we strive to understand and assist customers' with their specific banking needs. The firm's main goal is to provide the best possible financial products and services, exceptional customer service and a unique a personal touch.                




Secretary, Director & Chief Credit Officer

                                    Current                


Renasant Bank


                  Part of Renasant Corp., Renasant Bank is a company headquartered in Tupelo, MS, focused on state commercial banks. Edward Robinson McGraw is the CEO, in this role since 2000.                




Member-Community Bankers Counsel

                                    Current                


South Carolina Bankers Association


